  <!-- WHAT IT IS -->
  <div class="l-sec l-fade" style="background:#fff;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB">
    <div class="l-wrap-sm" style="text-align:center">
      <p class="l-sec-label">What is Groundwork?</p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:#4A5568;line-height:1.85;max-width:620px;margin:0 auto 28px">Groundwork runs regular check-ins across your team, project, or programme. Use it when you hire someone new, kick off a project, set objectives, run a performance improvement plan, or need to know if your team understood a brief or document. Everyone answers privately. Over time it cross-references what people said, what they did, the outputs they created, and what they understood against what you set, and shows you exactly where things are on track, where they are not, and where the gaps are before they become problems.</p>
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9B9590;line-height:2;max-width:580px;margin:0 auto">
        New hire &nbsp;·&nbsp; New project &nbsp;·&nbsp; New partner &nbsp;·&nbsp; New strategy &nbsp;·&nbsp; OKR tracking &nbsp;·&nbsp; Performance improvement plan &nbsp;·&nbsp; Pulse check &nbsp;·&nbsp; Realign team &nbsp;·&nbsp; Evaluate failing delivery &nbsp;·&nbsp; Team culture
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SUB-HERO -->
  <div class="l-sec l-fade" style="background:#F5F3EF;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB">
    <div class="l-wrap" style="text-align:center">
      <p class="l-sec-label">The real problem</p>
      <h2 class="l-sec-h2" style="max-width:680px;margin:0 auto 18px">Most projects don't fail because people don't care.<br>They fail because everyone leaves the room with a <em style="color:#0C447C;font-style:normal">different idea of what was agreed.</em></h2>
      <div class="l-prob-grid" style="margin-bottom:28px">
        <div class="l-prob-card"><div class="l-prob-title">You explained it.</div><div class="l-prob-desc">They heard something different. By the time you realised, weeks had passed.</div></div>
        <div class="l-prob-card"><div class="l-prob-title">They agreed in the meeting.</div><div class="l-prob-desc">Then nothing moved. You spent more time chasing than doing.</div></div>
        <div class="l-prob-card"><div class="l-prob-title">Everyone is working hard.</div><div class="l-prob-desc">Toward slightly different things. Nobody said anything because nobody wanted to be the one to say it.</div></div>
        <div class="l-prob-card"><div class="l-prob-title">You found out too late.</div><div class="l-prob-desc">The gap was always there. You just had no way to see it.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WHAT GROUNDWORK IS -->
  <div class="l-sec l-fade" style="border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB">
    <div class="l-wrap-sm" style="text-align:center">
      <p class="l-sec-label">What makes it different</p>
      <h2 class="l-sec-h2" style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto 16px">Most tools ask everyone the same questions in the same room. This one doesn't.</h2>
      <p class="l-sec-p" style="margin:0 auto 16px;text-align:center;max-width:560px">Everyone answers privately, without seeing anyone else's response. No performing for the room. No nodding along. No one defers in the meeting and disagrees later.</p>
      <p class="l-sec-p" style="margin:0 auto;text-align:center;max-width:560px">You get what people actually think. That is why it works.</p>

      <div style="background:#F5F3EF;border-radius:10px;padding:24px 28px;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
        <p style="font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:#0C447C;margin-bottom:8px;">Building a startup or running a fast-moving team?</p>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">When you are moving fast, the gap between what you said and what people heard compounds quickly. A new hire who misunderstood the brief. A team pulling in slightly different directions. A decision everyone nodded at but nobody executed the same way. Groundwork gives you a way to find out and fix it before it costs you, without calling another meeting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
  <div class="l-sec l-fade" style="border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB">
    <div class="l-wrap">
      <p class="l-sec-label">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="l-sec-h2">How it works.</h2>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr));gap:16px;margin-top:8px">
        <div style="background:white;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;border-radius:10px;padding:20px 18px;border-top:3px solid #0C447C">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#0C447C;margin-bottom:8px">Step 1</div>
          <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px">Write down what you need done</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.6">What did you tell them? What does success look like? What was agreed and by when?</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:white;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;border-radius:10px;padding:20px 18px;border-top:3px solid #0C447C">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#0C447C;margin-bottom:8px">Step 2</div>
          <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px">Your team answers privately</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.6">Each person says what they understood, what they have done, what is blocking them, and what support they need. Nobody sees each other's answers. That is why people tell the truth.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:white;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;border-radius:10px;padding:20px 18px;border-top:3px solid #5DCAA5">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#085041;margin-bottom:8px">Step 3</div>
          <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px">You see what landed and what did not</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.6">Who is on track. What is blocked. Where the understanding broke down, who thought what, and what to do about it.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:white;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;border-radius:10px;padding:20px 18px;border-top:3px solid #5DCAA5">
          <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#085041;margin-bottom:8px">Step 4</div>
          <div style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px">You know exactly what to fix</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.6">Not a vague note to improve communication. Specific people, specific misunderstandings, specific next steps.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
